## 6) Canonical Pattern Families (4688/4104/Sysmon 1)

Use unescaped alternation for regex groups: `(a|b|c)` not `(a\|b\|c)`.

Required families:
- shell execution / encoded command
- discovery / enumeration
- downloader / transfer
- lolbin execution
- persistence setup (service/task/run key)
- credential access / dump tooling
- defense evasion / anti-forensics
- lateral movement tooling

## 7) Mandatory Extraction Fields

At minimum retain per event where available:
- `event_id`, `channel`, `provider`, `timestamp`
- `IpAddress` / source IP equivalent
- `LogonType`, `LogonId`, `SubjectLogonId`
- `TargetUserName`, `TargetDomainName`, `WorkstationName`
- `Status`, `SubStatus`, failure/result code
- `CommandLine`, `NewProcessName`, `ParentProcessName`
- service/task/firewall object fields when applicable
- raw message text

## 8) Source-IP Attribution Priority

1. Direct StringInserts field (when index is known per §5).
2. Event-specific regex (e.g., MSSQL `[CLIENT:x.x.x.x]`).
3. LogonId chain lookup (4624 populates map; post-auth events chain via SubjectLogonId).
4. Fallback regex on message text.
5. If unresolved: mark unknown and keep event for context.

## 9) Known Cross-Source Conflicts

| Event | Conflict | Master Policy |
|-------|----------|---------------|
| 18453 vs 18454 | Both claim MSSQL success | Accept both until standardized |
| 4779 | G: `0x00` / labeler: `0x80` | Context by default; escalate to `0x80` only when lateral criteria met |
| 4726 | `0x10` vs `0x40` | Base `0x10`; add `0x40` when privileged-account tamper context exists |
| TS-LSM 21/25 vs Sysmon 21/25 | Event ID collision | **Gate on channel name** — Sysmon only from `Sysmon/Operational` |
| Defender 1006 vs SmbClient 1006 | Event ID collision | **Gate on channel name** — only from `Defender/Operational` |

